OL,3,CNorth Wales hospital 'failed to care'
OL,4,Cfor an adult with learning disabilities
OL,6,FMichelle Morris, Public Services
OL,7,FOmbudsman for Wales, said that "under
OL,8,Fthe equalities act in this country,
OL,9,Fanyone who has a disability an is in a
OL,10,Fcare setting such as a hospital
OL,11,Fexpects and has the right to have
OL,12,Freasonable adjustments made.
OL,14,F"So the staff should be aware of their
OL,15,Fdisability, should be aware of any
OL,16,Flimitations on their capacity to make
OL,17,Fdecisions about their own care, and
OL,18,Fthat didn't happen in that case.
